headline: New Year, New You: Walmart Launches Better Care Services and Rolls Back Prices on 1,000+ Wellness Essentials
summary: BENTONVILLE, Ark., January 08, 2026--Walmart is starting the new year by making healthcare easier and more affordable with the launch of Better Care Services. This one-stop digital destination is designed to help empower millions of customers to take control of their health journeys with ease, transparency and confidence.

headline: Plug Power (PLUG) Is Up 15.7% After Walmart Forfeits Massive Warrant Overhang - Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: In late December 2025, Plug Power and Walmart signed a 15-year Release Event License Agreement giving Walmart contingent access to escrowed GenKey materials for internal maintenance, while Plug Power retains intellectual property rights and receives initial and recurring license fees. A crucial feature of this deal is Walmart’s termination and forfeiture of its large Plug Power stock warrant, removing a very large potential future share issuance that had weighed on concerns about dilution...

headline: Walmart names Shishir Mehrotra to Board of Directors
summary: BENTONVILLE, Ark., January 08, 2026--Walmart Inc. (Nasdaq: WMT) announced the appointment of Shishir Mehrotra, Chief Executive Officer at Superhuman (formerly Grammarly), to the company’s Board of Directors, effective today. He will serve on the Board’s Compensation and Management Development Committee and the Technology and eCommerce Committee.

headline: Saks Is Struggling to Stay Afloat. The Dealmaker Behind the Scenes Did Just Fine.
summary: It has long been a truism that retailing increasingly will become digital and that for a physical store to survive it must be special (or “experiential”) and probably have a digital presence.  To wit, the Saks Fifth Avenue imbroglio, a complex stew of myriad brands and deals that was driven by one such individual.  To get you up to speed—this is one of those “fast moving” situations—Saks Global Enterprises, the holding company that operates Saks (as well as Bergdorf Goodman and Neiman Marcus), is strapped for cash, having skipped a $100 million payment to bondholders on Dec. 30 (Happy New Year to you!).

headline: Joby Aviation buys giant Vandalia building for $61.5M as local growth speeds up
